        "content_3XFPTU": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "The helmet that actually works.That workers actually like to wear.",
            "text": "<p>Hard hats have long been viewed as a necessary evil that most workers hate wearing. Hardknock helmets are engineered to protect far more effectively than any other safety helmet out there. And perhaps even more importantly, designed so workers actually like wearing them. Let’s find out how. And why.</p>",
            "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/tbi-enhanced.jpg",
            "bleed_image": false,
            "pad_image": false
          }
        },
        "content_DJPVny": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Only Hardknock has Nuro Core",
            "text": "<h4>Superior Energy Absorption </h4><p>Hardknock helmets are built with Nuro technology to absorb and dissipate impact energy more effectively than traditional helmets, and reduce the risk of brain injury from both linear force and rotational torque (learn more below). Nuro Core mitigates both, like no other.</p><h4>Multi-Directional Protection </h4><p>Most safety helmet liners are made to handle impact from one direction, perpendicular to the helmet. It’s an unrealistic consideration. The Nuro Core inside every Hardknock helmet is designed to handle impact from different angles. To radically enhance overall protection. </p>",
            "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/tbi-reduction.jpg",
            "bleed_image": false,
            "pad_image": true
          }
        },
        "content_rHDmMj": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Nuro Core Protects Against Rotational Torque",
            "text": "<h4>Mitigating Shear Forces: </h4><p>The science has been clear for decades. Most Traumatic Brain Injury occurs when the skull spins around the brain. Known as Rotational Torque, Nuro Core is a comprehensive and innovative technology that works to mitigate these “shear forces,” helping prevent concussions and diffusing axonal injuries.</p><h4>Both Kinds of Protection: </h4><p>Of course Hardknock helmets are also designed to protect against linear or “blunt forces.” By addressing both linear and rotational forces, Hardknock helmets provide truly dual protection, significantly lowering the risk of Traumatic Brain Injury. </p>",
            "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/tbi-comfort.jpg",
            "bleed_image": false,
            "pad_image": true
          }
        },
        "content_bVm78j": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Unbelievably Breathable. All Day Comfortable.",
            "text": "<h4>Ventilation and Breathability:</h4><p>The Nuro Core is 93% porous, contributing to just how well the Hardknock T2+ Pro ventilates and allows airflow to cool. So workers can feel a lot more comfortable across various working conditions and increase the likelihood that they’ll wear the helmet properly.</p><h4>Lightweight and Wobble-free:</h4><p>Despite all its advanced technology, Hardknock helmets are super lightweight. Painstakingly designed by biomedical engineers, they also use a fit system that eliminates wobble by doing away with all unnecessary hinges. Two big reasons why workers actually like wearing Hardknock. Imagine that.</p>",
            "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/tbi-versatility.jpg",
            "bleed_image": true,
            "pad_image": false
          }
        },
        "content_Kd6qaF": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Weight Balanced with a Lower Dome Height",
            "text": "<h4>That Balanced Feel:</h4><p>Each Hardknock is weight optimized, and it’s yet another reason why workers actually like wearing this helmet. Our experience designing athletic gear helped us understand how important proper weight distribution can be when it comes to minimizing fatigue. It’s a tangible intangible.</p><h4>Less Bumping and Clipping:</h4><p>Why are Hardknock helmets designed with a lower dome height? Because constantly bumping your helmet getting in and out of equipment or clipping it on overhangs means you’ll probably hate wearing it. And if you’re not wearing it, it can’t protect.</p>",
            "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/tbi-reduction.jpg",
            "bleed_image": false,
            "pad_image": false
          }
        }
      },
