        "intro_text": "<p>It’s pretty much always been assumed that construction workers can get away with a Type I rated helmet – primarily rated to protect the skull against impacts from above. But the jobsite is unpredictable. Hazards come from all angles, and impacts are rarely straight on. That’s why every Hardknock helmet is Type II rated. And here’s more on what that means.</p>",
